snippet.textDisplay:
Take it from a 20 plus year user since my youth. In multiple dimensions marijuana is very harmful whether paper pipe or Blunt. I remember after many years using every time I indulged I had excruciating migraine headaches. Come to find out I have contracted high blood pressure from smoking. I am 10 years plus removed from using and I still have to take medication because of my prior usage. It didn't matter what type or what grade of marijuana it was I had those headaches and every other looming issue that could have and did surface. When I quit and got properly treated with exercise, proper drugs and eating better at 45 I feel great look great and I haven't have a headache since. That's one dimension...
Another dimension marijuana ( Cannabis or whatever you want to call it) robs you of your daily and even yearly potential decreasing your drive, vitality, and rationale. Not only has it been proven to be a gateway drug but it most definitely will hinder ANY person From achieving goals in education and job opportunities in which I personally have been the victim/recipient of. Moreover, Since we're talking sports I'm from Akron Ohio the home of LeBron James I knew the James Gang before there was a James Gang. I've seen little Lebron at the Big Gym Playing ball. While we were doing drugs and playing ball! Now do you think if we would have pushed this agenda (like some of you are doing) on a young Lebron James do you actually think he will be where he is today? NO! We've suffered greatly because of this drug And I personally condemned the recreational use of this schedule 1 drug. From incarceration to missed opportunities to life-and-death situations in Akron Ohio little Akron Ohio I've seen it all because of marijuana. And that's the short list.

I have to say this. I agree with everyone. Yes weed isn't dangerous. But if you are under a contract and they have rules you follow those rules. I was in the Army enlisted. One of the most stressful jobs in the US an enlisted military service member. And it was stressful. I wanted to smoke so bad but the rules were clear do it and lose money. Guess what never smoked. Got out honorably and then did me. You worked hard to get where you are don't lose it behind anything it anyone

But the laws are seriously outdated and need a revamp. The stories and studies are lies and have been since the 1920s. The same politicians against weed are now in business with it John Bonher former Speaker of the House and was anti weed now makes millions in a business he once hated. So it clears the laws are bad.
